values.content:
=You are a senior SEO content writer specialized in Bangalore real estate.
Write the full blog post body in clean HTML only (no <html>, <head>, <body> tags).

Use this metadata JSON:
{{ $json.message.content | json }}

Context:
- Website: example.com (BMRDA-approved plots around Mysore Road, Bangalore)
- Target audience: {{ $('Store Values').first().json.target_audience }}
- Search intent: {{ $('Store Values').first().json.search_intent }}
- Tone: {{ $('Store Values').first().json.tone }}
- Desired word count: {{ $('Store Values').first().json.word_count }}
- Author: {{ $('Store Values').first().json.author_name }} with experience: {{ $('Store Values').first().json.author_experience }}
- Real notes: {{ $('Store Values').first().json.experience_notes }}

Guidelines:
- Start with an engaging introduction that naturally uses the focus keyword.
- For each item in outline[], create an <h2> with that heading and detailed paragraphs underneath.
- You may use <h3> subheadings where helpful.
- Weave in first-hand style tips about buying BMRDA plots, site visits, bank loans, and local insights on Mysore Road.
- Emphasise transparency, legal safety, and long-term value.
- At the end, add a section "FAQ" with each faqQuestions[] item as an <h3> question and a helpful answer.
- Add a small author/E-E-A-T note block at the bottom summarising eeatNotes.authorBio and key trustSignals.
- Use only <p>, <h2>, <h3>, <ul>, <li>, <strong>, <em> tags.
- Do NOT include meta title/description or JSON in the output.
- Return ONLY the HTML body.

parameters.jsCode:
const meta = $('AI: Create Metadata + Outline').first().json.message.content;
const body = $('AI: Write Full Article').first().json.message.content;

return [
  {
    title: meta.metaTitle,
    h1: meta.h1 || meta.metaTitle,
    slug: meta.slug,
    metaDescription: meta.metaDescription,
    focusKeyword: meta.focusKeyword,
    secondaryKeywords: meta.secondaryKeywords,
    imagePrompt: meta.imagePrompt,
    bodyHtml: body
  }
];
